  "statement_md": "Every semester the final-years pass the canteen discount code down to the juniors — but never in plain text, because canteen anna changes the code the moment it leaks. Their trick: take the real code (a single lowercase word) and slide every letter **forward** in the alphabet by `K` steps, wrapping around from `z` back to `a`. With `K = 2`, `a` becomes `c` and `y` becomes `a`.\n\nYour senior just messaged you the scrambled word along with the number `K`. Slide the letters back and print the real code before the juice counter queue gets long.",
